Create a class named Player with the following member variables/attributes (Default access)

Data Type                Variable Name

String                       name

String                       country

String                       skill

write a main function to test the above class.

Input and Output Format:

Refer sample input and output for formatting specifications.

All text in bold corresponds to input and the rest corresponds to output.



Sample Input and Output:

Enter the player's name

MS Dhoni

Enter the country name

India

Enter the skill

All Rounder



Player Details:

Player Name:MS Dhoni

Country Name: India

Skill: All Rounder

solution:
class Player:
    name="";country="";skill="";
    def __init__(self,name,country,skill):
        self.name=name
        self.country=country
        self.skill=skill
#main program
name=input("Enter the player's name\n")
country=input("Enter the country name\n")
skill=input("Enter the skill\n")
pl1=Player(name,country,skill)
print("Player Details:")
print(f"Player Name:{pl1.name}")
print(f"Country Name:{pl1.country}")
print(f"Skill:{pl1.skill}")
